tracking_table_clean <- 
  tracking_table%>%
  mutate(`building_permit_process` = `Permit Approved` - `Permit Filed`)%>%
  mutate(`Project Filed` =as.Date(`Project Filed`, "%m/%d/%Y"))%>%
  mutate(`Project Approved` = as.Date(`Project Approved`, "%m/%d/%Y"))%>%
  mutate(`planning_project_process` = `Project Approved` - `Project Filed`)%>%
  mutate(`earliest_date` = case_when(`Project Filed` > `Permit Filed` ~ `Permit Filed`,
                                     TRUE ~ `Project Filed`))%>%
  mutate(`earliest_date_type` = case_when(`Project Filed` > `Permit Filed` ~ "Permit Filed",
                                     TRUE ~ "Project Filed"))%>%
  mutate(`latest_date` = case_when(`Project Approved` > `Permit Approved` ~ `Project Approved`,
                                     TRUE ~ `Permit Approved`))%>%
  mutate(`latest_date_type` = case_when(`Project Approved` > `Permit Approved` ~ "Project Approved",
                                     TRUE ~ "Permit Approved"))%>%
  mutate(`entire_permitting_process_two_departments` = latest_date - earliest_date)%>%
  mutate(`time_project_approved_permit_filed` = `Permit Filed` - `Project Approved`)

summary_tracking <-NULL

summary_tracking <-
summary_tracking$latest_date_distribution <-
  sum(tracking_table_clean$latest_date_type == "Project Approved")%>%
  as.data.frame()%>%
  rename("latest_date_is_project_approved"=".")%>%
  mutate("latest_date_is_permit_approved" = sum(tracking_table_clean$latest_date_type == "Permit Approved"))
summary_tracking_longer <-
  summary_tracking%>%
  pivot_longer(
      c("latest_date_is_project_approved","latest_date_is_permit_approved"),
      names_to = "latest_date_type",
      values_to = "count_of_projects"
    ) 

latest_date_type_distrubution <-
  summary_tracking_longer %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(
    aes(
      x = `latest_date_type`,
      y = `count_of_projects`
    ),
    stat = "identity",
    fill = "lightblue"
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "latest date type",
    y = "number of projects",
    title = "Latest date type - distrubution"
  )

latest_date_type_distrubution

summary_entire_process<-
  tracking_table_clean_non_na_2%>%
  mutate(time_range = case_when(
    `entire_permitting_process_two_departments` < 80 ~ "30 to 80 days",
    `entire_permitting_process_two_departments` < 130 ~ "80 to 130 days",
    `entire_permitting_process_two_departments` < 180 ~ "130 to 180 days",
    `entire_permitting_process_two_departments` < 230 ~ "180 to 230 days",
    TRUE ~ "230 to 280 days"
  ))%>%
  select(PERMIT_NUMBER, PROJECT_ID, time_range)%>%
  group_by(time_range)%>%
  summarise(count_projects_within_time_range = n())
entire_process_time_range_distrubution <-
  summary_entire_process %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(
    aes(
      x = `time_range`%>%factor(levels = rev(c("30 to 80 days","80 to 130 days","130 to 180 days","180 to 230 days","230 to 280 days"))),
      y = `count_projects_within_time_range`
    ),
    stat = "identity",
    fill = "pink"
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "days",
    y = "number of projects",
    title = "Entire process time range - distrubution"
  )+
  coord_flip() +
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom",
    legend.direction = "vertical"
  )

tracking_table_clean_non_na<-
  tracking_table_clean%>%
  filter(!is.na(`time_project_approved_permit_filed`))%>%
  filter(!is.na(`entire_permitting_process_two_departments`))

tracking_table_clean<-
  tracking_table_clean_non_na %>% 
  mutate(time_project_approved_permit_filed_categories = case_when(
    `time_project_approved_permit_filed` < -100 ~ "< -100 days",
    `time_project_approved_permit_filed` < 0 ~ "-100 to 0 days",
    TRUE ~ ">= 0 days"
  )) %>%
  mutate(entire_permitting_process_two_departments_categories = case_when(
    `entire_permitting_process_two_departments` < 100~ "0 to 100 days",
    `entire_permitting_process_two_departments` < 200 ~ "100 to 200 days",
    TRUE ~ "> 200 days"
  ))
tracking_table_clean %>% 
  group_by(latest_date_type, entire_permitting_process_two_departments_categories) %>% 
  summarize(estimate = n()) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(
    aes(
      x = entire_permitting_process_two_departments_categories %>% factor(levels = rev(c("0 to 100 days", "100 to 200 days", "> 200 days"))),
      y = estimate,
      fill = latest_date_type
    ),
    stat = "identity",
    position = "fill"
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "entire process (days)",
    y = "number of projects",
    title = "Cross analysis: entire process X type of the last day",
    fill = "type of the last day"
  ) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom",
    legend.direction = "vertical"
  )  +
  guides(
    fill = guide_legend(
      reverse = T
    )
  )
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'latest_date_type'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

tracking_table_clean <-
  tracking_table_clean %>%
  mutate(planning_project_process_categories = case_when(
    planning_project_process < 100 ~ "< 100 days",
    planning_project_process < 200 ~ "100 to 200 days",
    TRUE ~ "> 200 days",
  )) %>%
  mutate(building_permit_process_categories = case_when(
    building_permit_process < 30 ~ "< 30 days",
    building_permit_process < 70 ~ "30 to 70 days",
    TRUE ~ "> 70 days",
  ))
building_permit_process <-
  tracking_table_clean %>% 
  group_by(building_permit_process_categories)%>%
  summarise(count_project = n()) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(
    aes(
      x = `building_permit_process_categories`%>%factor(levels = rev(c("< 30 days", "30 to 70 days", "> 70 days"))),
      y = count_project
    ),
    stat = "identity",
    fill = "lightgreen"
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "days",
    y = "number of projects",
    title = "Days - building permit process"
  )+
  coord_flip() +
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom",
    legend.direction = "vertical"
  )
